## Power Budget

The power budget tracks subsystem power draws across five operating modes.
Available power is set by the solar array end-of-life (EOL) output at Mars
distance: **{{ power.solar_array.performance.power_mars_eol }}**.

```{python}
#| label: power-margin

# Per-mode total power draws from the power budget
power_modes = {
    "Cruise": {{ systems.power_budget.row[17][2] }},
    "Science Mapping": {{ systems.power_budget.row[17][3] }},
    "Communications": {{ systems.power_budget.row[17][4] }},
    "TAG Maneuver": {{ systems.power_budget.row[17][5] }},
    "Safe Mode": {{ systems.power_budget.row[17][6] }},
}

# Solar array EOL power at Mars
solar_eol_w = float("{{ power.solar_array.performance.power_mars_eol }}".split()[0])

print("=== Power Margin Summary ===")
print(f"{'Mode':<22} {'Draw (W)':<12} {'Margin (W)':<12} Margin (%)")
print("-" * 58)
for mode, draw in power_modes.items():
    margin_w = solar_eol_w - draw
    margin_pct = (margin_w / solar_eol_w) * 100.0
    status = "[OK]" if margin_pct >= 30 else "[LOW]" if margin_pct >= 0 else "[OVER]"
    print(f"{mode:<22} {draw:<12.1f} {margin_w:<12.1f} {margin_pct:.1f}% {status}")
```

